The paper deals with machine learning algorithms and optimization of distance and similarity functions, which are common topics in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions experiments performed on various datasets, which suggests that it could belong to computer vision (cs.CV) or natural language processing (cs.CL) subfields. The use of a nonlinear feature space and the focus on classification suggest that it could also belong to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or neural networks (cs.NE).
